            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1584555970213-scheduling-and-timeliness" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#8c8bb473-8cd0-43be-955f-763be12d55b8" href="#accordion-content-1584555970213-scheduling-and-timeliness" aria-controls="accordion-content-1584555970213-scheduling-and-timeliness" aria-expanded="false">
                            Scheduling and timeliness
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1584555970213-scheduling-and-timeliness" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1584555970213-scheduling-and-timeliness">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1584555970213 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2733b6b5-533c-4a06-86a0-07ab2b69c4a2" >

    <ul> 
 <li>Provide students with time to adapt when making changes to the delivery of a course. Keep in mind that students may need to make changes to their living environment in order to participate online.</li> 
 <li>If there is a disruption that causes Ryerson to close, there will be an initial period when many students are in transition as they move home. During this time, they may have limited capacity to participate in online learning.</li> 
 <li>Summarize all of the changes to the course delivery in one place. Try to avoid ongoing changes.</li> 
 <li>Consider offering remote/virtual office hours. If this is not possible, let students know how long it will normally take you to respond to email.</li> 
 <li>To the extent possible, establish deadlines that fall within the normal academic day. This helps to promote healthy boundaries for students’ overall wellbeing.</li> 
 <li>Develop a plan for flexibility around assessments and deadlines.</li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#2733b6b5-533c-4a06-86a0-07ab2b69c4a2");});</script></div>

